cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the problem of guarding a simple polygon, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the design of algorithms and the analysis of their running time, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of epsilon-nets and approximation algorithms also suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
